For its ﬁrst bite, the snake is most feared.
The serpent bends and weaves with utmost grace.
The snake’s fangs bite deep.
The nix-snakes of the East can bite through tempered steel.
The snake defends itself by attacking.
Practitioners of Snake Style must internalize the raw speed and reﬂexes of a coiled snake.
The master of Snake Style is as quick as lightning and as deadly as a dozen serpents.